article.description: — Souley Boum and Bryson Williams scored 23 points apiece as UTEP beat Charlotte 77-62 on Sunday.
article.headline: UTEP beats Charlotte 77-62
article.story: EL PASO, Texas -- — Souley Boum and Bryson Williams scored 23 points apiece as UTEP beat Charlotte 77-62 on Sunday. Boum shot 6 for 9 from behind the arc. Williams also had 13 rebounds. Efe Odigie had 12 points for UTEP (12-10, 8-8 Conference USA), which won its fourth consecutive game. Brice Williams had 15 points and seven rebounds for the 49ers (9-13, 5-9), whose losing streak stretched to six games. Jahmir Young added 12 points. Jordan Shepherd had seven assists. The Miners improve to 2-0 against the 49ers this season. UTEP defeated Charlotte 70-47 on Saturday. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
